  "extras": {
    "summary": "AN ACT TO ENACT THE \"MISSISSIPPI SAFE SCHOOLS INFORMATION-SHARING ACT OF 2026\"; TO ESTABLISH A SECURE STATEWIDE ONLINE STUDENT SAFETY RISK-ASSESSMENT TRACKING AND INFORMATION-SHARING SYSTEM IN COORDINATION WITH THE JUVENILE COURT SYSTEM AND SCHOOL DISTRICTS; TO REQUIRE TIMELY DATA ENTRY OF RISK ASSESSMENTS; TO PROVIDE LIMITED ACCESS FOR PRIVACY PURPOSES; TO REQUIRE BEHAVIORAL THREAT ASSESSMENT AND MANAGEMENT (BTAM) TRAINING FOR CERTAIN DISTRICT LEADERSHIP; TO REQUIRE LOCAL LAW ENFORCEMENT NOTIFICATION TO A JUVENILE'S SCHOOL DISTRICT OF A JUVENILE FELONY ARREST WITHIN 24 HOURS AND AUTHORIZE TRANSMISSION THROUGH THE SYSTEM; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
  },
